                        <TextView
                            android:layout_width="match_parent"
                            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_margin="10dp"
                            android:text="There are many beautiful and adventurous places to visit near Bansi Narayan Temple. Some of them include: &#xA; &#xA;Urgam Valley: Urgam Valley is known for its scenic beauty and tranquil surroundings. It offers picturesque views of the surrounding mountains, terraced fields, and apple orchards. Visitors can take leisurely walks, enjoy the serene ambiance, and interact with the local villagers to experience their culture and way of life.&#xA; &#xA;Kalpeshwar Mahadev Temple: Kalpeshwar Mahadev Temple is a Hindu Temple dedicated to Lord Shiva is situated in Urgam Valley, Chamoli District Garhwal Region of Uttarakhand State. Kalpeshwar is the Last Temple as Shivaâ€™s divine forms in order of 5 Kedar Temple. Kalpeshwar temple is the only Panch Kedar temple accessible throughout the year. Around 300m trek from the road head this small stone temple approached through a cave passage, Lord Shiva is worshipped here in the form of matted tress (jata).&#xA; &#xA;Nandi Kund: Nandi Kund is a high-altitude lake located in the Indian state of Uttarakhand. The lake is situated at an altitude of 4,300 meters above sea level and is surrounded by snow-capped peaks and glaciers. The trek to Nandi Kund is a challenging and scenic trek that takes you through remote villages, high-altitude meadows, and breath-taking landscapes. The trek starts from the village of Ransi in the Chamoli district of Uttarakhand via Madhyamaheshwar and takes you through the Pandav Sera trail before branching off towards Nandi Kund.&#xA; &#xA;Gopinath Temple: Gopinath Temple dedicated to Lord Shiva is situated in Gopeshwar Town, Chamoli Garhwal district of Uttarakhand State. The temple was built by Katuri Kings of ancient Uttarakhand between 9th to 11th centuries. Architecture of Gopinath temple is same as other famous Panch Kedars of Uttarakhand.  There is a trident (Trishul), in the courtyard of the temple, about 5 m high, made of eight different metals, which dates back to the 12th century. Gopinath Temple lies exactly mid between Badrinath Dham and Kedarnath dham with distance of 151km from both Temples. "
                            android:textColor="@color/black"
                            android:textSize="15sp" />
